<br>
How dare he leave my guild and not give me a good explanation why(I am not the leader, however) <br>
<br>
<br>
Question: Why does he/she owe you an explanation? If it was explained to the guildleader, shouldn't that be adequate? Possibly, this person was uncomfortable and didn't seek confrontation<br>
<br>
Next Quote <br>
He left in the morning, while I was gone, so I couldn't exactly ask him in guild chat before he left. Ferdynna, our leader, said that he left because.<br>
<br>
<br>
It's bad form to discuss deguilding matters in guildchat. Any Guildleader that is concerned with unity or morale will tell you so.It creates unnecessary tension and conflict. It is a matter for private chat or tells. <br>
<br>
Final Quote<br>
Now I am glad you are a rogue, because I know how you couldn't solo anything that wasn't green. <br>
<br>
Are you speaking of rogues in general or just him? Personally, I can testify that if one is properly equipped rogues can solo. <br>
<br>
Furthermore...<br>
This is a personal matter between the guild (whatever one you are in) and Lothor Finepoint. Unless he is scamming you out of your armor or creating so much havoc that it's inexcusable..... I'd keep it between the offending parties.<br>
